** RAM (memory) types : 
 soldered RAM --> built in with mother board , if you want to replace it you must change the whole mother board 
 SO-DIMM (small outline dual in-line)--> removable memory that can be replaced ( it is held in place by clips within its slots ) 
** Storage types : 
 HDD (Hard Disk Drive) --> magnetic disk , spinning drive platter (slower because it depends on physical movement to read data)
 SSD (Solid State Drive) --> no moving parts , more speed , less latency , smaller than HDD , have sata cable
 SSD M.2 --> the smallest size , it plugs directly into a motherboard slot without power or sata data cables (very easy to install and replace)
 SATA --> protocol of the hard available on (HDD , SSD , SSD M.2)
 NVMe --> protocol of the hard available on (SSD M.2 only) more speed than SATA
** To upgrade from HDD to SSD without reinstalling the OS or losing data, use a SATA-to-USB adapter to perform a 'Disk Cloning' process
** Mini PCI or Mini PCI Express (replaceable)
802.11 wireless + bluetooth --> for wifi connection (LAN) , bluetooth (PAN) personal
** Screens
portable LCD (liquid crystal displays) --> light source in the back ground
3 technologies for LCD :
TN LCD (twisted nematic) --> the  oldest , the original LCD , fast respoonse + poor viewing angle
IPS LCD (in plane switching) --> more expensive , excellent colour representation
VA LCD (vertical alignment) --> in the middle between TN , IPS  ,  good colour + slower than TN
OLED (organic light emitting diode)  --> doesn't have backlight , this organic compound emits
light when recieving electric , thinner + lighter , very easy to carry out ex:tablets , phones
*note* The laptop screen is a housing for two types of cables: the first one is for video on the
left side (commonly), and it connects the motherboard and the screen directly for videos, webcam 
and microphone. The second one is for the Wi-Fi + Bluetooth (antennas - black and white wires) on 
the right side; these wires start from the Wi-Fi card on the motherboard, pass through the hinges, 
and are routed around the screen to reach the top for the highest signal strength.
webcam is abuilt in camera + microphone , audio + vedio  




